&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Remote – US (Open to applicants located in the USA)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fueled is a leading digital strategy, design, and engineering agency. Recently united with 10up – &lt;a href=&quot;https://10up.com/blog/2025/new-fueled-brand-10up-becomes-wordpress-practice/&quot;&gt;now the brand of our WordPress practice&lt;/a&gt; – we are a 300+ person team that has designed and built hundreds of digital products and experiences for brands like Google, Apple, The New York Times, ESPN, Victoria’s Secret, MGM Resorts, Albertsons, and CLEAR.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;As a growing force in the digital services space, we’re building a brand that resonates, a growth engine that converts, and a team that scales impact. We&#39;re looking for a strategic and action-oriented &lt;strong&gt;VP, Marketing &amp;amp; Growth&lt;/strong&gt; to lead our full-funnel growth function from first impression to forming a long-term relationship.&amp;nbsp; This role is pivotal in strengthening our voice in the market, fueling demand, supporting conversion and enabling client retention and expansion.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Sitting at the intersection of marketing, brand, content, and revenue, this role partners cross-functionally with Product, Strategy, Client Services, and Executive Leadership to align messaging with motion, attention with action, and storytelling with sales. You’ll shape how we show up, what we say, and how we grow.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;With a sharp understanding of modern marketing infrastructure, a love for compelling narratives, and a metrics-driven mindset, you’ll help us grow our brand—and our business.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Elevate the Brand:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Define and evolve our brand positioning, voice, and visual identity. Champion our story in a way that resonates with ideal customers and amplifies market presence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own Full-Funnel Marketing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Lead integrated strategies across paid, earned, and owned channels, brand campaigns, performance marketing, email, events, and more, to drive awareness, engagement, and conversion.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Demand and Acquisition:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Launch always-on and campaign-based programs that attract, nurture, and convert the right audiences into pipeline and revenue.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Activate GTM Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Partner closely with business development and GTM teams to craft sequenced, personalized marketing plays that accelerate sales momentum and nurture prospects.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build Thought Leadership &amp;amp; Content:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Oversee the development of strategic content and enablement tools, from white papers to case studies that support both credibility and conversion.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Refine ICP and Messaging:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Define and continuously evolve our Ideal Customer Profile (ICP), building segment-specific messaging that speaks to value and need.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Modernize Marketing Infrastructure:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Select and optimize tools for campaign execution, data enrichment, analytics, and personalization, bringing scale and precision to every motion.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expand Ecosystem Influence:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Cultivate relationships with analysts, partners, and collaborators who amplify our brand and enhance inbound quality.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Co-Own Pipeline and Revenue Targets:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Partner with sales leadership to track performance, optimize marketing contribution, and align on accountability for bottom-line impact.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead and Inspire a High-Performing Team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Guide a multidisciplinary team of marketers and business developers. Foster a culture of curiosity, experimentation, and results.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You bring 10+ years of marketing, business development, or growth leadership experience, ideally in digital agencies, consultancies, or productized services environments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You have a proven track record of building integrated marketing programs that generate brand awareness, demand, and qualified pipeline.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You think across the funnel, comfortable working in brand strategy one day and performance metrics the next. Content, campaign orchestration, and digital media are in your wheelhouse.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You’re a collaborative operator who thrives in cross-functional environments. You’ve partnered closely with product, strategy, and client service teams to drive aligned growth outcomes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You’re fluent in modern marketing stacks and tools—including AI-enhanced platforms that support personalization, automation, targeting, and reporting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You’re a compelling communicator who understands how to craft a message, influence stakeholders, and rally a team around a shared vision.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You’re detail-oriented, metrics-focused, and excited by the opportunity to scale fast with clarity and accountability.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits &amp;amp; Salary&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Competitive salary and benefits. Compensation is determined based on a variety of factors including relevant experience, other job-related qualifications, geographic location, and business needs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join our Team! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are passionate about Fueled&#39;s mission and think you have what it takes to be successful in this role, even if you don&#39;t check all the boxes - please apply. We&#39;d appreciate the opportunity to personally review your application. Everyone gets a response.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any data provided will be processed in accordance with applicable law and our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://fueled.com/privacy-policy/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;privacy policy&lt;/a&gt;. Curious about what to expect during our talent process? Check it out&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/fueled/What-to-Expect-from-the-Interview-Process-at-Fueled-1d84dccd9d8b80f8a0b0d40b244f4caf?pvs=4&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Remote – Anywhere&amp;nbsp;(Open to applicants located anywhere aligned with the Americas time zones)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fueled is a leading digital strategy, design, and engineering agency. Recently united with 10up – &lt;a href=&quot;https://10up.com/blog/2025/new-fueled-brand-10up-becomes-wordpress-practice/&quot;&gt;now the brand of our WordPress practice&lt;/a&gt; – we are a 300+ person team that has designed and built hundreds of digital products and experiences for brands like Google, Apple, The New York Times, ESPN, Victoria’s Secret, MGM Resorts, Albertsons, and CLEAR.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Director of Product &lt;/strong&gt;to lead and scale our Product Management team, process, and practice. This critical role will be responsible for shaping the services and solutions we leverage to define, build, and grow digital experiences for our clients. This role entails a mix of leadership, management, and craft ownership on our most complex client engagements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you will do:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the owner of Fueled’s Product Management services and solutions. Establish and maintain best practices, and ensure that process, methodologies, and tooling are constantly refined to best meet the needs of our clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive AI adoption by championing its practical application—identifying opportunities to create efficiencies, unlock new capabilities, and fundamentally shift how we approach product delivery for ourselves and our clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee (and be accountable for) our output and quality of delivery on client engagements at every stage of the project lifecycle. Ensure that all products we create are well architected and produce real end-user value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, mentor, and manage a growing team of high-performing Product Management practitioners. Work with our Resourcing Manager to most effectively allocate the team’s time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide strategic oversight and guidance for Product Management practitioners on projects, and support execution as necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish, operationalize, and own internal initiatives to better define, position, and socialize Product Management as a capability at Fueled (both internally and externally).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on industry trends and ensure our services and solutions are modern, innovative, and ahead of the curve relative to our competitors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Delivery leads to maintain appropriate staffing levels and utilization. Support the allocation of Product Management resources to different engagements and initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Technology and Design leadership to foster synergy and collaboration across the broader strategy practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent Fueled’s Product practice externally at conferences, events, and speaking engagements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support our Sales and Marketing teams in pitching and positioning our services and solutions to prospective clients (and the world!).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;notion-enable-hover&quot; data-token-index=&quot;0&quot;&gt;About you:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 10+ years of experience in digital Product Management, preferably in an agency setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 3+ years of management experience, with a proven track record of leading Product Management teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have deep expertise in Product Management methodologies and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a strong understanding of research and design principles for creating intuitive and user-friendly digital experiences, and demonstrated experience in doing so for mobile apps and websites.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ve developed a deep foundational knowledge of a technology, web, and mobile to the extent that most client questions can be answered without consulting an engineer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a strategic understanding of large scale content-heavy digital experiences and the role of content strategy in ensuring success of such projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have excellent communication, presentation, and interpersonal skills with the ability to influence executive-level stakeholders and manage client relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are proficient in product development and design software (Figma, Figjam).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience working with and leading others as part of a distributed (remote) team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are excited about AI and other next-gen tech!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits &amp;amp; Salary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive salary and benefits. Compensation is determined based on a variety of factors including relevant experience, other job-related qualifications, geographic location, and business needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join our team!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;If you are passionate about Fueled&#39;s mission and think you have what it takes to be successful in this role, even if you don&#39;t check all the boxes - please apply. We&#39;d appreciate the opportunity to personally review your application. Everyone gets a response.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;We don&#39;t want you to miss any communication from us! To ensure you receive updates on your application, please add &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:jobs@fueled.com&quot;&gt;jobs@fueled.com&lt;/a&gt; to your contacts list!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Any data provided will be processed in accordance with applicable law and our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://fueled.com/privacy-policy/&quot;&gt;privacy policy&lt;/a&gt;. Curious&amp;nbsp;about what to expect during our talent process? Check it out &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/fueled/What-to-Expect-from-the-Interview-Process-at-Fueled-1d84dccd9d8b80f8a0b0d40b244f4caf?pvs=4&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Remote - India (Open to applicants located in India)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fueled is a leading digital strategy, design, and engineering agency. Recently united with 10up – &lt;a href=&quot;https://10up.com/blog/2025/new-fueled-brand-10up-becomes-wordpress-practice/&quot;&gt;now the brand of our WordPress practice&lt;/a&gt; – we are a 300+ person team that has designed and built hundreds of digital products and experiences for brands like Google, Apple, The New York Times, ESPN, Victoria’s Secret, MGM Resorts, Albertsons, and CLEAR.As a &lt;strong&gt;Marketing Program Manager&lt;/strong&gt;, you’ll partner closely with the cofounder of a US-based digital agency to bring marketing ideas to life—moving projects from concept to execution with precision and care. You&#39;ll help keep everything running smoothly, ensuring deliverables arrive on time and nothing slips through the cracks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, remote role. You&#39;ll need to be available for one 1-hour meeting per day, Monday–Thursday, during US East Coast (ET) business hours. Outside of those daily meetings, your schedule is flexible and self-directed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize and track diverse marketing initiatives using tools like Trello or Notion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project-manage a wide range of marketing tasks, from one-off projects to ongoing and recurring initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow up with freelancers, creators, vendors, and contractors to keep timelines on track&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and source new creative vendors (e.g., identify TikTok ad creators, coordinating trials, and help evaluate outcomes)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor project progress and proactively flag any blockers or missing elements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Occasionally, review deliverables for completeness and clarity before final submission&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll achieve:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll find satisfaction in making things happen and enabling others to focus on strategy and creativity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will thrive in a behind-the-scenes role where follow-through and attention to detail make a big impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will have value autonomy and want flexibility while working on meaningful, high-visibility projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ll be excited to work closely with a cofounder and gain exposure to a variety of marketing and creative initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have strong organizational skills and the ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a proactive mindset—you take initiative and don’t wait for direction to add value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have clear and effective English communication skills, both written and spoken&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re comfortable with tools like ChatGPT, Trello, Google Docs, and Notion (or similar project management tools)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience working remotely, ideally with distributed or international teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You take a reliable, accountable approach—others know they can count on you to follow through&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with creatives, agencies, or freelancers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with digital marketing tools or workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience managing small teams or coordinating complex projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join our Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;If you are passionate about Fueled&#39;s mission and think you have what it takes to be successful in this role, even if you don&#39;t check all the boxes - please apply. We&#39;d appreciate the opportunity to personally review your application. Everyone gets a response.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;We don&#39;t want you to miss any communication from us! To ensure you receive updates on your application, please add &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:jobs@fueled.com&quot;&gt;jobs@fueled.com&lt;/a&gt; to your contacts list!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Any data provided will be processed in accordance with applicable law and our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://fueled.com/privacy-policy/&quot;&gt;privacy policy&lt;/a&gt;. Curious&amp;nbsp;about what to expect during our talent process? Check it out &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/fueled/What-to-Expect-from-the-Interview-Process-at-Fueled-1d84dccd9d8b80f8a0b0d40b244f4caf?pvs=4&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our mission at Sourcegraph is to make it so that &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Mission-values-e9d37e6b972a4ef395c3076aea2bd07d?pvs=4&quot;&gt;everyone can code&lt;/a&gt;, not just ~0.1% of the population.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are transforming how the world’s most important companies build software by industrializing development with AI. Today, most professional developers spend a disproportionate amount of time understanding code and performing repetitive, low-level tasks—leaving less time for innovation and meaningful impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re changing that. Sourcegraph brings AI-powered search and agents to the enterprise, helping teams automate the mundane and amplify what developers do best— solving hard problems and creating great products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here’s how we’re making a difference:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accelerating developers &lt;/strong&gt;with AI agents that deliver insights and precision—enabling 5x faster test creation, 30% increase in merge requests, and saving 20 minutes per developer daily.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Automating repetitive tasks,&lt;/strong&gt; from remediating vulnerabilities (saving teams 1,000+ hours annually) to speeding up migrations that would take years to months.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enabling innovation&lt;/strong&gt; by addressing complex problems like automated bug triage, vulnerability detection, and AI-driven code reviews seamlessly integrated into workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trusted by 7/10 top software companies by market cap, 4/6 top US banks and many of the companies leading global innovation, like Stripe, Indeed, Tesla, and 1Password, and with $225M in funding from investors like &lt;a href=&quot;https://techcrunch.com/2021/07/13/sourcegraph-raises-125m-series-d-on-2-6b-valuation-for-universal-code-search-tool/&quot;&gt;a16z&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://about.sourcegraph.com/blog/series-c-with-sequoia/&quot;&gt;Sequoia&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.redpoint.com/companies/sourcegraph/&quot;&gt;Redpoint&lt;/a&gt;, we are building the tools that will define the next era of enterprise software development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re passionate about solving the hardest problems in software and shaping the future of technology, join us. Let’s build something extraordinary together.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours &amp;amp; location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;🌎 While we hire &lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/How-we-engage-talent-outside-of-the-US-218f7193695a46cbb1ef39ef9c1f72d4&quot;&gt;almost anywhere&lt;/a&gt; in the world, we have a preference for someone to reside in the following locations for this role. However, if you feel qualified, we welcome you to apply regardless of location. No matter what, working hours must overlap with Mountain Time for at least 20 hours/week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred locations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;North America&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;South America&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We do not subscribe to “I do my best work when I work 40 hours a week.”&amp;nbsp; People we hire at Sourcegraph believe that building outstanding things means working very hard — smarter and more hours than the competition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why this job is exciting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Security Engineer, you will join our exceptional&lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/Security-81d50b5ac5474b07bdbadd5359993c80&quot;&gt; security team&lt;/a&gt; tasked with building world-class security into our product offerings by working on vulnerability management, application security testing and vulnerability scanning automation, bug bounty programs, and security reviews for both application and infrastructure security. You will proactively improve the security of our codebase, our product, our cloud, and our customers&#39; on-premise deployments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Within one month, you will…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will contribute to the team&#39;s goals and deliverables for securing the largest deployment of Sourcegraph (sourcegraph.com), enabling customers to upload private code repositories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will discover, fix, and mitigate infrastructure vulnerabilities by updating libraries, base images, and analyzing containers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will enhance our application security with audits, best practices, code fixes, and continuous education&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will perform reactive incident response if a security event occurs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Within three months, you will…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will enhance our security measures and policies to support organizations on sourcegraph.com and ampcode.com&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will work with other teams to triage, troubleshoot and mitigate customer concerns and questions about our security&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You and your manager will work together on a career plan with actionable goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Within six months, you will…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will work with other teams and engineers to implement secure coding guidelines and best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will perform proactive research to detect new attack vectors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will perform threat modeling for existing and future applications&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will assess and integrate new tools and technologies to improve our operational efficiencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will help maintain compliance with SOC 2, ISO 27001 &amp;amp; GDPR standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Equal parts engineer and security professional, you are excited about joining a team that is building a world class security system trusted by some of the biggest tech companies in the world.&amp;nbsp; You and your teammates are Sourcegraph’s first line of defense against bad actors using all the newest and dirtiest tricks to hack us and (more importantly) our customers.&amp;nbsp; You want to be a part of the foundational team, the first steps we are taking to build something big, something trusted, something critical to software and our customers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your skill-set:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practical experience securing SaaS applications, including infrastructure security, application security, and/or compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using and automating a wide range of defensive security tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing software as an engineer (i.e., writing code and contributing directly to applications)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working across engineering teams to support secure coding across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are high agency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You communicate effectively in writing and documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nice to haves:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in a startup environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Go, TypeScript, Terraform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Kubernetes, GCP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience securing AI products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Level&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;📊 This job is an IC3.&amp;nbsp; You can read more about &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Leveling-Guide-0e1b5c76ada64b9caac387f8b7c4fc66&quot;&gt;our job leveling philosophy&lt;/a&gt; in our Handbook.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;💸 We pay you an above-average salary&lt;/strong&gt; because we want to hire the best people who are fully focused on helping Sourcegraph succeed, not worried about paying bills. As an &lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/Mission-values-e9d37e6b972a4ef395c3076aea2bd07d&quot;&gt;open and transparent&lt;/a&gt; company that values &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Compensation-Pay-Transparency-at-Sourcegraph-d58d0774f51b4b489d41c3628d30ff8d?pvs=4&quot;&gt;competitive compensation&lt;/a&gt;, our compensation ranges are visible to every single Sourcegraph teammate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your salary is determined by your pay band for the IC3 job level. For determining pay bands, we use a number of market and data-driven salary sources, along with your location zone, and target the high-end of the range to ensure we’re always paying above market regardless of where you live in the world. Both U.S. and international locations are divided into one of four zones, determined by the cost of labor index for each area. The salary for a successful candidate will be based on level, job-related skills, experience, qualifications, and location zone. Please note that the salaries below may be adjusted in the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;💰 The target compensation for this role is based on the IC3 pay band for your zone. The start of the IC3 pay band for each zone is listed below:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Zone 2: $144,000&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Zone 3: $108,000&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Zone 4: $72,000&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please speak with a recruiter for additional information regarding zone locations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;📈 In addition to our cash compensation, we offer equity (because when we succeed as a company, we want you to succeed, too) and generous &lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/Benefits-Perks-dd1da4b6b3a64780abed010a144d34ba&quot;&gt;perks &amp;amp; benefits&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview process&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Below is the interview process you can expect for this role (you can read more about &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/Types-of-interviews-f279f080583d49ee9f2c60e30c8cb1f7&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;the types of interviews&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; in our Handbook). It may look like a lot of steps, but rest assured that we move quickly and the steps are designed to help you get the information needed to determine if we’re the right fit for you… Interviewing is a two-way street, after all!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We expect the interview process to take &amp;lt;5 hours in total.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;👋 Introduction Stage&lt;/strong&gt; - we have initial conversations to get to know you better…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[20m] &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Types-of-interviews-sample-questions-f279f080583d49ee9f2c60e30c8cb1f7?pvs=4#99be5ff628b2414194a0ba79d9f25f13&quot;&gt;Recruiter Screen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[30m] &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Types-of-interviews-sample-questions-f279f080583d49ee9f2c60e30c8cb1f7?pvs=4#1919882c0cf147c487eb1df40db8a694&quot;&gt;Hiring Manager Screen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[60m] &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Types-of-interviews-sample-questions-f279f080583d49ee9f2c60e30c8cb1f7?pvs=4#c678a2a86e0e47e4958507e869bf7ded&quot;&gt;Resume Deep Dive&lt;/a&gt; / Technical Screen&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🧑‍💻 Team Interview Stage&lt;/strong&gt; - we then delve into your experience in more depth and introduce you to members of the team, including cross-functional partners…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[60m] Technical Interview: General&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[60m] Technical Interview: Complex Problem Deep Dive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[45m] Cross-functional Team Collaboration / Values&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎉 Final Interview Stage &lt;/strong&gt;- we move you to our final round, where you gain a better understanding of our business and values holistically…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[15m] &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/How-to-work-with-Quinn-Slack-CEO-807673e0864d473f959cc4efd9642a5a?pvs=4#6f185c0e2011411eac5be9c675f9056c&quot;&gt;Leadership&lt;/a&gt; with co-founder&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We check references and conduct your background check&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note - you are welcome to request additional conversations with anyone you would like to meet, but didn’t get to meet during the interview process.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learn more about us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can learn more about what it is like to work at Sourcegraph by reading &lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/d7614e3e9dc04c09ac2d42d57f1816e6?v=2a6d426dbae14390b155120b0c029ce0&quot;&gt;our handbook&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an ambitious team who are collectively working hard to build the most influential company in the world.&amp;nbsp; You can read more about our &lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/What-it-s-like-working-at-Sourcegraph-119a8e11265880b18911eee4d9b7c460#119a8e1126588062b935fc66104b6115&quot;&gt;culture&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/Compensation-Pay-Transparency-at-Sourcegraph-d58d0774f51b4b489d41c3628d30ff8d?pvs=74&quot;&gt;competitive compensation&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/Benefits-Perks-dd1da4b6b3a64780abed010a144d34ba?pvs=74&quot;&gt;benefits&lt;/a&gt; here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sourcegraph is an equal opportunity workplace; we welcome people from all backgrounds.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sourcegraph participates in &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/E-Verify-2ab3286dde3446d6bac2898c83610107&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;E-Verify&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; for U.S. Employees. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
